pat = r'/(\w+)_\d+.jpg'

dblock = DataBlock((ImageBlock,CategoryBlock),
                    splitter=RandomSplitter(),
                    get_items=get_image_files,
                    item_tfms=Resize(224),
                    batch_tfms=aug_transforms(),

Using TensorBoard

{% raw %} 
import tensorboard
from fastai2.callback.tracker import SaveModelCallback
from fastai2.callback.tensorboard import TensorBoardCallback
{% endraw %}

What is tensorboard?

TensorBoard is a library built to work with Google's TensorFlow deep learning library. It lets us track and share our deep learning model and results. This is great when working with large teams, and sometimes tends to be a must.

Like all callback solutions, we need to add code to the training loop for TensorBoard to work. To solve this there is a Tensorboard callback builtin the fastai2 library. Similar to the SaveModelCallback, we can just add the callback to our cbs parameter in our fit method.

Before this, we need to define the tensorboard directory and the project_id. The first defines where the TensorBoard project results will be stored, while the second will define which project we are currently working on.

{% raw %} 
project_id = "TensorboardCallback"
tboard_path = Path('../tensorboard/' + project_id)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
callbacks = (TensorBoardCallback(log_dir=tboard_path))
{% endraw %}

Training

{% raw %} 
#show
def group_callbacks(path:Path, save:bool):
    tbcb = TensorBoardCallback(log_dir=path)
    savecb = SaveModelCallback(fname=path.name, every_epoch=True, with_opt=True)
    if save: return (tbcb, savecb)
    return (tbcb,)

def train_with(epochs:int=4, path:Path=tboard_path, save:bool=False):
    cbs = group_callbacks(path,save)
    learner = Learner(dls, resnet34(pretrained=True), metrics=error_rate)
    learner.fit_one_cycle(num_epochs, cbs=cbs)
    learner.show_results()
    torch.cuda.empty_cache()
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
train_with(epochs=4)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
#show
learner = Learner(dls, resnet34(pretrained=True), metrics=error_rate)
learner.fit_one_cycle(4, cbs=callbacks)
learner.show_results()

To see the results of the training you can run the cli command from tensorboard tensorboard --logdir=tensorboard

Adding SaveModel Callback

To add the SaveModel Callback we can just set save to True. This simply adds the callback to the cbs Tuple.

{% raw %} 
# cbs = (tensorboard, savemodel)
train_with(epochs=4, save=True)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
#show
learner = Learner(dls, resnet34(pretrained=True), metrics=error_rate)
learner.fit_one_cycle(4, cbs=callbacks)
learner.show_results()
